Chuks Okocha in Abuja Over twenty  officers of the Economic Financial Crime Commission have just arrived the MKO Abiola International Stadium, Abuja, the venue of the Peoples Democratic Party Special National Convention. The officers arrived the venue around 4.30pm. The purpose of their visit is still unknown. No fewer than 811 Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) delegates are undergoing accreditation at the national convention groundThe exercise will enable the party’s national delegates to decide the presidential flag bearer of the party.The delegates are drawn from the 774 local government areas of the country. See photos 